post_text:
A Message from Mr. Jones, Superintendent

Parents/Guardians:

I hope you and your family are enjoying the nice weather!

I would like to share the most current Preliminary Guidance from the Pennsylvania Department of Education on returning to school. Northern Potter is required to use this guidance to complete a Reopening Health and Safety Plan. It is our intention to have students and staff return to school as ‚Äúnormal‚Äù as possible on August 26, 2020. In the Green and Yellow Phase, all students will be in school everyday according to the adopted 2020-2021 school calendar. If the governor places us in the Red Phase, students and staff will be required to teach and learn remotely.

Please take a moment to read the preliminary guidance provided in the link and contact me with any questions you may have at 848-7506 or njones@northernpottersd.org.

post_text:
YEARBOOK DISTRIBUTION IS TODAY!
The day we have all been waiting for has arrived! The yearbooks will be distributed, by grade level, THIS morning through the Library windows.
Grades 10-12 may come to the high school at 10 AM. Grades 7-9 may come to the high school at 11 AM. Please come to pick up your yearbook during your scheduled time. Drive up to the front of the school and the library windows will be marked so you can get your book. If you are unable to pick up your book in person and need to send someone to get it for you, please message the district Facebook page. NO YEARBOOKS will be given to a person who did not buy them unless you send a message for permission.
If you are interested in buying a yearbook, we have a few extras. The cost is $55, check or cash.
Please share on your news feed.

A Message from Mrs. Bailey, Principal

MS/HS Clarification Notes

Completed Work Packets can be submitted Monday-Friday between 8am-2pm. There will be a drop-off box by the front entrance.

Final Due Date for all work is May 19th.

Teachers will need to have grades completed by May 22nd.

Final Report Cards will be mailed out the week of June 1st.

There is no set due date for Work Packet #2 prior to May 19th. Please mail or drop-off the work (Packets #1-3) any time before or on May 19th. If work needs to be turned in after May 19th, please call the HS office to make arrangements.

If you have any questions or concerns, please call the MS/HS Office (814-848-7534).

post_text:
Updated information on school closures

Governor Wolf today announced that all schools will remain closed for the remainder of the 2019-20 academic year to mitigate the spread of COVID-19. Students and families can continue to pick up meals at our district's designated sites.

Note: Northern Potter will provide lunches tomorrow, April 10 and resume our lunch distribution process on Tuesday, April 14. Lunches will not be distributed on Monday, April 13.

Northern Potter has submitted a continuity of education plan to the Pennsylvania Department of Education (PDE). Our goal is to continue teaching and learning through remediation and enrichment the best we can, given the circumstances. With the governor‚Äôs announcement of closing school for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year, we are pursuing additional resources from PDE to enhance learning opportunities for our students.

When I have more information, I will follow up with more information about questions related to 4th 9 weeks grading, graduation, and the logistics of picking up your personal items.

post_text:
Attention 8th grade families who participated in the Gertrude Hawk fundraiser

Due to the stay home order and the lack of safety involved in receiving cardboard boxes and making door-to-door deliveries, the Gertrude Hawk order has been canceled. Refunds will be processed. Mrs. Pomeroy will be calling each family who participated within the next few days to discuss the refund process.

Note: Those people who ordered online and shipped to their home have already received their products. Students will receive the profit from those sales. Those online sales that paid online, but scheduled to have them shipped with the school order have been cancelled. Those orders will be refunded back to the customers cards directly from Gertrude Hawk.

We are very sorry about this situation. It was beyond our control. We tried alternate solutions, but safety is our number one concern right now. This was the best action to fit that concern.

Questions can be directed to Mrs. Pomeroy at apomeroy@northernpottersd.org.

post_text:
Breaking News from Mr. Jones, Superintendent

Yesterday, Governor Wolf announced that all schools will remain closed until further notice as an effort to mitigate the spread of COVID-19.

As of March 24, every school district in Pennsylvania was required to create a Continuity of Education Plan.

Northern Potter implemented our Continuity of Education Plan on March 16 by providing remediation and enrichment to students for 15 school days. At the end of the week, I will provide information on how we are going to continue our plan through the month of April.

I appreciate teachers, parents, and students efforts for making the most of this difficult time to provide education opportunities for our students!

Lunch News from Mr. Jones, Superintendent

Governor Wolf's order calling all non-life-sustaining businesses in Pennsylvania to close their locations as of 8 p.m. March 19, does not prohibit school districts from continuing to offer food services to children during the statewide school closure.

At this point, Northern Potter will continue serving meals to our students including today, March 20.

If you have not pre ordered for today's meals you can pick up meals at the school as we have done throughout the week.

I will continue to contact you with clarifications as I receive new information.

Thank you,

Mr. Jones
